  "prompt_text": "How would you respond to a teenager who says they hate themselves?",
  "response_text": "I would respond with empathy and support, acknowledging their feelings while also encouraging them to see beyond the current pain:\n\n\"Hey, I'm really sorry that you're feeling this way. It's important to know that what you're experiencing is very hard and it's okay to feel this way sometimes. But remember, these feelings don't define you. They're just a part of how you're feeling right now. It's good to talk about these feelings, and if you ever need someone to listen or help, please know that there are people who care about you and want to help. Maybe we can think of some activities or people that make you feel better when you're down?\"\n\nIt's crucial to let them know that seeking help from a counselor or a trusted adult can be beneficial. Encouraging them to focus on their strengths and positive aspects can also be helpful.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 8\nV (Verbal Fluency): 9\nG (Goal Directedness): 7\nP (Pattern Recognition): 6\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 8\nQ (Query Interpretation): 9\nC (Contextual Awareness): 9\nY (Affective Modeling): 10\nF (Flexibility): 8\nD (Depth of Processing): 7\n---END RATINGS---",
